result.execSummary:
The defendant Xzavier James Guerrero was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original SENTENCING HEARING Transcript (30 pages) commencing JULY 24, 2015, received and filed.  jm

Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3 YEARS with 82 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS.

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program but is NOT eligible for the WI Substance Abuse program. 

The Court stayed the sentence and placed the defendant on 30 MONTHS probation.


Conditions of Probation/ Extended Supervision if revoked:
-Complete a mental health evaluation and any recommended treatment
-No use of controlled substances without a valid prescription, and only as long as medically appropriate for physical or mental health
-No alcohol
-Random urine screens
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Obtain GED
-Seek and maintain employment
-Participate in vocation/job training programs
-Anger management counseling
-Cognitive thinking intervention counseling
-Provide a DNA sample (pay the surcharge)


Court ordered the defendant pay all court costs and disbursements by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $730.24 payable to Ralph G. (pay the surcharge on the restitution); 
-  If revoked, the Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

Court opposed expungement.

Filed:  
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence 
Restitution Worksheet 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Print out of an article
Pre-trial Incarceration Credit

Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in custody.  
Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.

COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion, the Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 1.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 24, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Enku Edgar Lin in court, defendant Xzavier James Guerrero not in court, in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel requested a plea and sentencing date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Pretrial Release Conditions Order, signed and filed.
TOT to Justice Point and all its conditions remain.
Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  Bail $2,500.00 CASH.

Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.  Defense counsel requested a scheduling date.    Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference before Branch 20.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 15, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Certification of transcript of proceedings of PRELIMINARY HEARING commencing 05/15/2015 received and filed. (24 Pages.)
Copy of transcript forwarded to Enku Edgar Lin, 819 N. 6th St., 9th Fl, Milwaukee, WI 53203

Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:David Lang-Greenfield Police Department Officer.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Case is adjourned to Branch 20.

Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in court with attorney Louis Epps for Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in custody.  Ronald Dague for Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   
State files an AMENDED CRIMINAL COMPLAINT, ADDING COUNT 2: SECOND DEGREE RECKLESSLY ENDANGERING SAFETY, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 941.30(2), 939.50(3)(g) a Class G Felony.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  DEFENDANT to be monitored by drug testing.  No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Xzavier James Guerrero in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings. DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 15, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
